TI  - AGV Dynamic Scheduling and Path Planning Algorithm Based on 5G Technology in Intelligent Factory
AU  - J. Chen
AU  - Z. Liu
AU  - Y. Tian
AU  - Q. Yu
T2  - 2022 International Conference on Intelligent Manufacturing and Industrial Big Data (ICIMIBD)
AB  - With the characteristics of large bandwidth, high reliability, and low latency, 5G network technology has become the preferred network environment for AGV operations in intelligent factories. In this context, this paper presents an application framework of AGV scheduling and path planning optimization based on 5G and analyzes AGV dynamic scheduling process. Aiming at the AGV scheduling problem of flexible job shops in manufacturing enterprises, the optimization goal is to minimize the total time of all AGVs to complete the job scheduling task. The mathematical model and algorithm flow of dynamic scheduling and path planning of AGV management and control system to avoid conflicts and deadlocks are constructed. The AGV management and control system solves the scheduling scheme according to the heuristic artificial intelligence (AI) algorithm and outputs the optimal path planning result of multiple AGVs cooperative operations in the system. The results show that the combination of artificial intelligence algorithms can optimize the optimal path selection, realize the real-time dynamic scheduling of AGV in the factory, and make the material operation in the factory more efficient and smoother. Finally, a case study in a flexible workshop production line is constructed and studied to validate the proposed approach.
