AB  - This paper proposes a multi-objective optimization model considering idle time, time of use electricity price, battery degradation, and carbon quotas for the scheduling optimization of port electric logistics trucks under the “dual carbon” target. To solve the model, an improved adaptive genetic algorithm (IAGA) was designed, which improves the solving performance through adaptive operators and local search. The simulation results show that compared with the standard genetic algorithm (SGA) and first come first served (FCFS) strategies, the proposed method reduces the idle time and significantly reduces the total cost, verifying its effectiveness in improving port operation efficiency and promoting green operations.
