AU  - K. Zhang
AU  - J. Liu
AU  - Z. Liu
AU  - F. Song
AU  - X. Fu
T2  - 2025 8th International Conference on Transportation Information and Safety (ICTIS)
AB  - In the hub-and-spoke radial maritime network, feeder vessel transportation is easily affected by factors such as changes in port cargo pallets and the navigational environment that does not support the smooth departure of vessels from the port, which leads to the uncertainty of the service time of vessels in the port. This paper analyzes the route planning process of feeder vessels based on digital twin technology. A multi-objective vessel route optimization model with port time window constraints is constructed in this paper. Taking the minimization of total transportation cost as the objective function, the vessel service time in port is dynamically adjusted by combining physical space data. The mathematical model is solved using a genetic algorithm kernel and MATLAB tools to generate a vessel route planning scheme. The method helps to reduce the cost of unplanned vessel feeder transportation and the probability of transportation delays, and to a certain extent ensures that the vessel completes the feeder port service within the specified time.
