AU  - N. A. Telyatnikova
AU  - I. A. Vishnyakov
AU  - E. V. Mitryukhina
AU  - A. A. Olenich
T2  - 2025 International Conference on Quality Management, Transport and Information Security, Information Technologies (QM&TIS&IT)
AB  - The article is devoted to the problem of ensuring the efficiency of cargo transportation logistics management based on information technologies. It is proposed to use digital twins as an important tool for monitoring and managing key transport objects using rolling stock as an example. The life cycle of a transport object and the life cycle of an intelligent software product are analyzed. The cyclic model of development and implementation of a software product is studied, which requires the use of change management and configuration management methods over a long period of supporting the operation of a transport object. The configuration of an information system containing digital twins and their management is proposed. An example of the operation of a refrigerated container as a complex cargo transportation object requiring monitoring and optimal online management in the process of providing a transport service is considered. Proposals are given for the development of digital twins of transport objects in order to improve the efficiency of logistics activities of transport companies.
