TI  - Research on Image Recognition and Data Optimization of Intelligent Management System of Power Warehouse Driven by Meta-Universe
AU  - Y. Zhang
AU  - Q. Guo
AU  - R. Ding
AU  - L. Yu
AU  - X. Tian
T2  - 2025 Asia Conference on Energy Conversion Systems and Power Electronics (AECSPE)
AB  - Aiming at the pain points in power equipment warehouse management, such as fragile labels, low efficiency of manual inspection and difficulty in monitoring extreme environment, this paper proposes a meta-universe-driven intelligent management system for power warehouses, focusing on overcoming two technical bottlenecks: image recognition and dynamic data optimization under complex illumination. The system adopts "five-layer collaboration" architecture, takes digital twinning as the core, and integrates 5G+TSN network, edge computing and Unity three-dimensional modeling to realize real-time mapping and closed-loop regulation between physical warehouse and virtual space. On the level of image recognition, an improved YOLOv7-CBAM model is proposed, and Retinex adaptive illumination compensation and BiFPN multi-scale feature fusion are introduced. The average recognition accuracy is 93.4% in rain and fog, strong reflection and low illumination scenes, which is significantly better than the baseline of Faster R-CNN and YOLOv7. On the data optimization level, GCN-GRU spatio-temporal joint inventory forecasting model and GAN-Q-learning fusion path planning strategy are constructed, so that the MAPE of transformer inventory forecasting in the next seven days is controlled within 5%, and the average time consumption and energy consumption of AGV emergency tasks are reduced to 29.1 min and 12.6 kWh respectively, and the task achievement rate is improved to 97%. The experiment is based on the data of 12 000 m2 real power warehouse. The coincidence degree between the digital twin preview trajectory and the actual operation is 98.2%, and the potential collision risk of the whole system can be reduced by 23%. The research results provide a reproducible technical path for the metauniverse landing of power industry.
