AB  - This article mainly discusses the application and optimization methods of OpenHarmony operating system in terminal devices in the power industry. Through analysis and experimental testing of existing technologies, it has been found that OpenHarmony has significant advantages in device interconnection, real-time performance, and stability. Through the evaluation of system response speed, this article finds that the optimized OpenHarmony system has an average response time of 195 milliseconds under 100 concurrent operations. In the evaluation of data processing efficiency, the optimized OpenHarmony system achieves a processing capacity of 6.2 million when processing 1 million data per second. In the system security assessment, the optimized OpenHarmony system exhibits high protection capabilities against various network attacks. From the data conclusion, it can be deliberately seen that the optimized OpenHarmony system has shown significant improvements in response speed, data processing efficiency, and security.
