AB  - In the process of port intelligent transformation, real-time completion of missing truck trajectory data plays a vital role in the qualitative data collection of port production operations and the establishment of port digital twin systems. Focusing on the port-specific scenario, this article introduces a method of completing the trajectory of the truck based on the long short-term memory (LSTM), followed by empirical data analysis method. The neural network was deployed to train and predict the trajectory data of trucks in the port. At the same time, it explores the possibility that making a rough prediction of the long-term missing data by considering the historical data and analyzing the truck&#x2019;s speed distribution characteristics. Compared with previous studies, the method proposed in this paper provides new ideas and methods for collecting missing trajectories of trucks in ports.
