TI  - Unified Cognitive Orchestration System: The Next Paradigm for End-to-End Port Management and Predictive Truck Appointment Scheduling
AU  - V. T. M
AU  - G. G. R
AU  - S. T
T2  - 2026 International Conference on Intelligent and Innovative Technologies in Computing, Electrical and Electronics (IITCEE)
AB  - Global port logistics are critically hindered by digital fragmentation, where isolated information silos between terminal operators, customs authorities, and shipping lines create significant operational friction and costly inefficiencies. The primary barrier to true integration is not technological but strategic: a justifiable reluctance from stakeholders to cede control over their proprietary data systems. This work addresses this challenge by proposing and implementing a neutral orchestration architecture designed to unify disparate data sources without requiring direct, privileged access to core systems. The primary artifact of this research is the Unified Cognitive Orchestration System (UCOS), a fully functional, real-time web application built on a Python Flask backend and a dynamic JavaScript frontend utilizing Server-Sent Events for live data propagation. UCOS successfully demonstrates the ability to aggregate multi-terminal slot data, provide an intelligent 'pre-check' tool that validates a container's complete readiness (location, customs, and freight status), and embed real-time validation directly into the truck appointment booking process to eliminate user error at the source. The results confirm that this decoupled, API-driven model is a feasible and scalable blueprint for a real-world Port Community System, validating the thesis that a neutral intermediary can transform fragmented, reactive operations into a predictive, efficient, and cohesive logistics ecosystem.
