TI  - Generative AI-Driven Digital Twin in the Manufacturing Internet of Things: A Comprehensive Survey
AU  - X. Fu
AU  - M. Qin
AU  - P. Pace
AU  - C. Savaglio
AU  - W. Li
AU  - G. Fortino
T2  - IEEE Internet of Things Journal
AB  - Digital twins (DTs) have evolved from static digital mirrors into executable cyber–physical counterparts that predict, optimize, and control complex systems. However, the practical deployment of DT in the Internet of Things (IoT) environments suffers from limited data fidelity, model brittleness, and resource constraints across the edge–cloud continuum. Generative DT (GDT) is DT augmented with generative artificial intelligence (GenAI). They enable the synthesis of high-fidelity data, bridge model-driven and data-driven paradigms, and provide adaptive decision support under uncertainty. This article systematically reviews the research progress on GDT in the manufacturing IoT (MIoT), covering system architectures, key enabling technologies, and representative application scenarios. It also summarizes the main limitations of existing studies and outlines future research directions.
