TI  - PEX3D File Format as Standardised Data Exchange Tool in Power Electronics Design Automation
AU  - G. Papadopoulos
AU  - F. Krismer
AU  - J. Biela
T2  - 2025 Energy Conversion Congress & Expo Europe (ECCE Europe)
AB  - Virtual prototyping and multi-objective optimisation are essential for optimally designing Power Electronic (PE) converters with high power density and low losses. However, the lack of a standardised file format limits an efficient data exchange between different tools/models (e.g. analytical component models, simulations, etc.) required for the different domains (e.g. electrical, thermal, magnetic, etc.). This constrains the execution of Power Electronics Design Automation (PEDA) toolchains. To overcome this limitation a X3D file format adapted for PEDA is presented and a file structure for its use as a standardised eCAD format is proposed. The proposed file structure supports modular designs, simplifying component reuse, debugging, and the integration of new tools. A buck converter example demonstrates the practical application of the file format.
