AB  - Digital Twin (DT) provides a key theoretical framework and technical route for the establishment of Autonomous Waterborne Transportation Systems (AWTS) which integrates and interacts with physical and virtual spaces. In this paper, a new DT concept of AWTS is proposed, considering the characteristics of DT and the essence of AWTS. A three layers technology architecture is proposed for AWTS oriented towards DT, comprising the physical layer, virtual layer, and application layer. Moreover, key technologies and challenges for building AWTS based on DT are comprehensively analyzed and discussed. Consequently, this paper provides insight into the application of DT in AWTS, including technology architecture, key technologies and future research directions.
