AU  - H. Wu
T2  - 2025 5th International Conference on Energy, Power and Electrical Engineering (EPEE)
AB  - This paper presents a collaborative restoration method for distribution network cyber-physical system under extreme disasters, addressing the entire recovery timeline. First, a model for regional network division is constructed—defining unknown, fault, outage, and energized zones—to articulate the communication network's function during fault localization, isolation, and restoration. Second, a repair crew dispatch model is established. Incorporating the coupled failure characteristics of the cyber-physical system, a cooperative recovery model is proposed to optimize the scheduling of repair resources. Case studies on a modified IEEE 33-bus system show that the proposed method effectively accelerates post-disaster recovery and enhances system resilience, thus validating its effectiveness and superiority.
