AB  - The modern grid is becoming a cyber-physical energy system with coupled power, intelligent electronic devices and communication network. Innovative control and protection systems require a more comprehensive approach for validation and verification under realistic conditions. This work presents a cyber-physical platform to evaluate the operation of a power system with the consideration of heterogeneous controllers and communication networks. The container concept is introduced to overcome the drawbacks of existing real-time co-simulation methods. With two separate network interfaces, containers can combine real-time power system simulation and network emulation in a single framework. The platform is scalable and flexible, and can test different system scales and network topologies with various control scenarios. An agent-based distributed secondary control in a hybrid MVAC/DC network was configured and implemented to prove the effective operation of the platform.
