TI  - Research on the “Five-Phase” Framework for Urban Traffic Congestion Management Based on Artificial Intelligence
AU  - J. Luo
AU  - J. Qiu
AU  - T. Wang
AU  - X. Liu
T2  - 2025 6th International Conference on Computers and Artificial Intelligence Technology (CAIT)
AB  - With the acceleration of urbanization, traffic congestion has become a critical issue constraining urban development. This paper proposes an artificial intelligence-based “five-phase” urban traffic congestion management framework, which includes five phases: congestion detection, traffic classification and cause analysis, preliminary countermeasure derivation using large models, simulation analysis of expected outcomes, and post-implementation evaluation and experience summarization. This framework integrates multidisciplinary technologies such as big data, deep learning, and large language models, establishing a complete closed-loop management system from congestion identification to effectiveness evaluation. Through a typical application case analysis in Shenzhen’s Nanshan Science and Technology Park area, the effectiveness of the framework is validated. The study shows that this framework improves congestion management efficiency by 40% and achieves an accuracy rate of 85%, providing a replicable systemic solution for smart urban transportation.
