AB  - An advanced vessel monitoring and collision avoidance system that enhances maritime safety and operational efficiency through sensor integration and machine learning. GPS ensures precise positioning, while RADAR detects obstacles to prevent collisions. An accelerometer, vibration sensor, and gas sensor monitor structural integrity and hazardous gas leaks, while environmental factors are measured using the DHT11 and BMP180 sensors. LoRa communication enables real-time data transmission, and machine learning algorithms improve weather prediction and collision avoidance. Edge and cloud-based analytics process large datasets for rapid decision-making, with an automated alarm system alerting the crew to anomalies. This integrated approach optimizes navigation, enhances decision-making, and advances intelligent nautical systems for safer maritime transportation.
