TI  - Topology Reconfiguration for Cyber-physical Energy System with Multi-source Interference
AU  - Q. Shan
AU  - F. Teng
T2  - 2019 Chinese Control Conference (CCC)
AB  - The cyber-physical energy system (CPES) can comprehensively perceive the environment and energy information, and realize the deep understanding of the relationship between the state of the energy system. However, due to the uncertainty of large-scale new energy sources, the disturbance of network communication signals in long-distance transmission, and the limitation of computing ability in processing large data, in CPES, delay and noise disturbance may result a failure of large-scale distributed real-time computing of CPES. Therefore, the distributed optimization disturbed by multi-source interference in CPES need to be solved urgently. In this paper, the general noise and time-varying delay are used to characterize the complex multi-source interference in the CPES. Aiming at the distributed optimization problem, the consensus of the concerned multi-agent modeling is analyzed, and the criteria to ensure the supply and demand of the energy system are obtained. Furthermore, this paper proposes a method of reconstructing and optimizing network topology, which can effectively suppress or even eliminate the disturbance of multi-source interference. When this method is applied to the energy interconnected system, we find that it effectively solves the problem of concerned distributed optimization. Finally, a practical example is given to illustrate the effectiveness of the obtained results.
