TI  - Reinforcement Learning-Based Critical Scenario Generation for Safety Verification of Autonomous Cyber-Physical Systems
AU  - H. Wang
AU  - S. Peng
AU  - J. An
AU  - Y. Hao
AU  - X. Zhang
T2  - 2025 International Conference on Cyber Resilience and Endogenous Safety & Security (CRESS)
AB  - Ensuring the security and reliability of cyber-physical systems (CPS) remains a significant challenge, primarily due to the difficulty of reproducing rare yet critical security-related scenarios in real-world testing. To address this issue, this paper proposes a Reinforcement Learning-based Critical Scenario Generation Framework (MCSG) for simulation-driven security verification of CPS. The method abstracts real-world driving data into a maneuver operation-level representation and models modal relationships among scenario parameters. By designing a hierarchical reinforcement learning agent with a composite reward function, it balances scenario realism, feasibility, and criticality. Experimental results in the CARLA simulation environment demonstrate that the generated scenarios effectively expose safety vulnerabilities in automated collision avoidance systems. Compared to existing optimization-based and learning-based methods, this framework reduces longitudinal and lateral trajectory errors by 32.7% and 15.3%, respectively, while increasing collision rates by 5.1%. These findings indicate that the proposed MCSG method efficiently identifies high-risk boundary cases, positioning it as a practical tool for CPS safety verification.
C3  - 2025 International Conference on Cyber Resilience and Endogenous Safety & Security (CRESS)
