TY  - CONF
TI  - Enhanced Maritime Safety Through Intelligent Life Jackets Featuring Real-Time Location and Long-Range IoT Connectivity
AU  - J. Surendiran
T2  - 2025 3rd International Conference on Intelligent Cyber Physical Systems and Internet of Things (ICoICI)
AB  - This project aims to detect hypothermia in climbers and transmit their health status to their group. Hypothermia occurs when the body loses heat rapidly in freezing conditions, leading to unconsciousness below 35°C. To address this, we designed a life jacket equipped with a temperature sensor, Peltier module, and pulse sensor for real-time health monitoring. The temperature sensor detects body temperature, and the Peltier module adjusts accordingly to provide heating or cooling. A GPS module assists climbers in choosing a suitable path while tracking their location. The collected health data is transmitted to the rescue team or caregiver for timely intervention. Communication is facilitated using the LoRa network for reliable long-range connectivity. Alert messages are delivered through an Android app, ensuring quick response. This system enhances climbers' safety by providing continuous health monitoring and informed decision-making. It is designed to prevent life-threatening conditions during mountain expeditions.
