TY  - CONF
TI  - Polynomial Formal Verification of Prefix Adders
AU  - A. Mahzoon
AU  - R. Drechsler
T2  - 2021 IEEE 30th Asian Test Symposium (ATS)
AB  - Nowadays, prefix adders are widely used in different designs and applications due to their flexible carry propagation hardware. The variety of these adders makes it possible to find the best choice based on the design parameters, e.g., area, delay, number of wiring tracks. Proving the correctness of prefix adders is an important task after their design as they usually have a complex and error-prone structure. It has been experimentally shown that Binary Decision Diagrams (BDDs) are very efficient in the formal verification of adders, including prefix adders. However, it has been never proved theoretically. In this paper, we calculate the computational complexity of proving the correctness of prefix adders using BDDs. Based on these calculations, we show that the formal verification of prefix adders can be done in time polynomial in n, where n is the size of the adder (i.e., the number of bits per input). We also compare the theoretical calculations with the experimental results to clarify the differences between the complexities in theory and practice.
