AB  - With the current diversified development of spacecraft, the overall design and state control of spacecraft have become increasingly difficult, and the traditional overall design and management model has gradually been unable to meet the research and development needs of current and future spacecraft. This paper addresses the challenges of traditional spacecraft design models, such as low data interaction efficiency and complex version control, by proposing an AI-based system architecture. The solution integrates multi-source data fusion, intelligent knowledge management, and digital twin technology to enable processdriven design and full-lifecycle data management, thereby improving design efficiency and collaboration capabilities.
