TI  - Risk Control Cyber Physical System for Active Distributed Network
AU  - Y. -N. Wang
T2  - 2018 2nd IEEE Conference on Energy Internet and Energy System Integration (EI2)
AB  - Open information environment and high variability and uncertainty of active distributed network (ADN) make it an urgent need to make up the vacancy of ADN risk control system. This paper is the first to apply cyber physical system (CPS) into ADN risk control. The new method raised in this paper, two-stage risk control and one-stage risk alarm, can solve the conflict of accuracy and speed of risk control under different operating environment. Distributed collection and control system meets the needs of control terminal plug and play. Self-locking function prevents the power system from information system disaster automatically. New system designs, including risk state classification according to time dimension, risk status conversion protocol and parallel control, improve the heterogeneous physical problems of CPS. Real-time risk emergency control strategy implements rapid and effective real-time risk control. This is the first realization of unified model with multiple risk indicators and different aspects of risk management. The system proposed also realizes the good coordination between cyber and physical system. This paper puts forward a feasible active risk self-management system for ADN Jor the first time, which may provide advices and ideas for the construction and development of smart grid.
