AB  - In this paper, we study key theoretical approaches such as modeling and identification of business process-oriented coupling structure problems from the perspective of resource allocation efficiency of computing, network and storage that can be provided by terminal sensing devices and edge servers of edge computing. A particle swarm intelligent optimization algorithm APSO is proposed for multi-terminal business sequencing. Based on the collected resource information of mobile terminals and edge servers, considering the interaction between multiple business activity requests, we study how to efficiently allocate the resources of edge servers, dynamically make the approximate optimal process sequencing for all applications, and make the average completion time of all business activities and the average energy consumption of mobile terminals and and edge servers are made to be approximately optimal. Finally, a series of experiments are conducted to evaluate the performance of APSO. The experimental results show that the proposed particle swarm optimization algorithm has a good advantage in terms of average completion time and average energy consumption in a multi-terminal business scenario with limited edge server resources.
