AB  - ILIAD focuses on developing an ecosystem of interoperable Digital Twins for the Ocean by connecting to existing ocean data infrastructures, enhancing ocean data infrastructures with additional observation technologies and citizen science, employing numerical models and executing AI models, and aiding operational decision-making of marine and maritime activities. This work focuses on the diverse ILIAD Pilots and emphasizes sensors, data collection, and data management. Emphasis is given on new, low-cost sensors, their objectives, the novel technical aspects, the generated data, and how they can be used in the ILIAD project framework and the operation of ILIAD DTs.
