AB  - This paper presents an optimized deployment strategy for edge computing nodes, taking into account both information stability and power stability. By quantifying information accuracy and stability, a computational model for assessing information stability is constructed. Additionally, the power stability scale is established through a method of observing small-disturbance voltage variations. Based on the hybrid entropy theory, the system's information-power hybrid entropy is calculated to solve for the optimal deployment of network edge computing nodes. Through standard case simulations on the IEEE39 power system, the study verifies the effectiveness of the proposed edge computing node deployment scheme. The simulation results demonstrate that this method significantly enhances network response speed, strengthens reactive power support, and effectively stabilizes system frequency deviations, thereby validating its practical applicability.
