TY  - CONF
TI  - Research on Data Augmentation Model for Gas Equipment Based on Deep Dimensionality Reduction and Fusion of Generative Strategies
AU  - G. Zhang
AU  - H. Zhang
AU  - B. Qin
AU  - Y. Pan
T2  - 2025 6th International Conference on Computer Communication and Network Security (CCNS)
AB  - In the context of the rapid deployment of urban gas industrial Internet of Things (IoT) systems, ensuring the confidentiality and integrity of sensitive device data has become a key challenge. In large-scale industrial gas scenarios, the encrypted transmission and secure storage of multi-source heterogeneous data from devices face threats. Inadequate data or data leakage may lead to vulnerabilities in risk assessment models (such as deviations in leakage prediction and failure of corrosion monitoring), which in turn can trigger both physical and network security risks. The gas industrial IoT system covers various links such as pressure vessels, intelligent pipe networks, and terminal sensors. The absence or tampering of unencrypted lifecycle data (such as plaintext design parameters and unsigned maintenance records) will expose operation and maintenance to the blind spots of cyberattacks, making it difficult to achieve data-driven security protection and preventive maintenance. To address the scarcity of gas industrial IoT data and the demand for secure data generation, this paper constructs a solution that integrates deep dimensionality reduction and generation strategies. Generally speaking, this method first uses the DeepPCA scheme for nonlinear encoding to retain the correlations between deep features. Subsequently, the KMeans algorithm is utilized to divide the clustering centers in the low-dimensional space, and controllable noise is added according to the distribution characteristics of the clusters to generate new samples. Finally, the LSTM-BPNN hybrid model is employed to conduct multi-dimensional quality inspections, including distribution similarity, prediction error, and feature integrity, on the generated data to verify the effectiveness of the data generated by the strategy proposed in this paper.
