AB  - Big data are sets of information that are too large or complex to process by traditional means. Finding results that determine trends is like finding a needle in a haystack. The field of big data is constantly changing, as a result, new methods and techniques are being developed. One such area that has not received substantial attention is a comprehensive guide on how to build a system that can handle big data using deep learning. Big data has gained great traction and support, due to it being a method to discover new trends with machine learning and artificial intelligence. This guide provides some high level design considerations to build an integrated big data system for a theoretical ship that uses prognostics to determine Remaining Useful Life (RUL) of components.
