TI  - User Satisfaction-Aware Resource Allocation for 5G Green Vehicle Platooning
AU  - R. Geng
AU  - H. Ren
AU  - J. Yan
T2  - 2019 International Conference on Internet of Things (iThings) and IEEE Green Computing and Communications (GreenCom) and IEEE Cyber, Physical and Social Computing (CPSCom) and IEEE Smart Data (SmartData)
AB  - Platooning has been identified as a green vehicular traffic management strategy to improve energy efficiency, environmental sustainability, road capacity, and on-road safety, in which the platoon' stability is ensured through the exchange of control information among vehicles. Proximity-based device-to-device (D2D) communications with high transmission rate, is more suitable for delay-sensitive inter-vehicle communications. In order to achieve the above benefits, there are several fundamental challenges that should be addressed: 1) how to design an appropriate communication mode combined with D2D technology, to face complicated road conditions; and 2) how to efficiently allocate the limited resources to guarantee each users' service satisfaction. In this paper, a predecessor-following communication mode-based on D2D is proposed to guarantee high-rate transmission of control information. After that, a time division-based intra-platoon resource allocation mechanisms is briefly introduced, which aims at allocating resources for D2D users (DUEs) efficiently within the platoon. Then, based on the social relationships among users, an optimization problem about resource allocation inter platoon is formulated and solved with the objective to maximize the user satisfaction. Numerical results show that the proposed mechanism can not only improve user satisfaction, but also guarantee the minimum transmission rate of each platoon.
