AB  - This article describes an approach to the problem of constructing an observer's trajectory, optimized for the accuracy of estimates of the COP (coordinates and parameters of target movement), as to the problem of planning a regression experiment. The article discusses the problem of determining the COP only from noisy bearing measurements. The accuracy of statistical estimates in this work is understood as the value of the generalized variance of estimates. It is the quality of the estimates that will determine the probability of their falling into a predetermined neighborhood of the true values of the parameters. Evaluation of COP is performed by one of the methods of statistical processing of measurements, which provide estimates of the coefficients of regression models describing the mutual movement of the observer and the target.
