AB  - Location tracking is of paramount importance to many applications such as healthcare, retail and navigation. Outdoor tracking can be easily implemented using the Global Positioning System (GPS). However, indoor tracking has been a challenging problem to tackle because GPS requires the line of sight to the satellites and therefore it does not work well in indoor environments. In this paper, a high-precision indoor tracking scheme, SRK, is proposed to identify, locate, and track a person in an indoor environment at a low cost. Technically, SRK consists of three components: Stepscan floor tiles, RFID, and Kalman-filter-based prediction. The performance of SRK is investigated through extensive simulations. Our simulation results indicate that SRK increases the tracking capability by at least 24%. Furthermore, SRK helps to reduce the cost of indoor tracking significantly.
