AB  - This paper presents a cognitive architecture for humanoid robots operating in smart factory environments. The proposed system integrates motion pattern analysis, cognitive embeddings, and probabilistic modeling to enable natural, human-inspired robot behavior. By embedding robot configurations and process control data into a unified cognitive space, the architecture facilitates complex task execution and movement coordination. Experimental results confirm the effectiveness of the approach in classifying motion patterns and generating interpretable cognitive constructs, enhancing robot adaptability in industrial settings.
