AB  - As there are some problems existing in the cyber physical system (CPS), for example, network resource wasting, computing resource wasting and component failure, the co-design problem between fault-accommodation and communication saving is studied in this paper based on the idea of edge computing. Firstly, the idea of edge computing is introduced into CPS. The estimation work of system state and failure information are completed in the smart sensor which is in the edge of CPS network, and the work of transmission data filtering was also completed in the smart sensor. Secondly, the failure estimation method with $H_{\infty}$-performance was derived based on Lyapunov theory, and the co-design method between failure accommodation and communication resource saving was proposed based on the failure estimation value. Finally, the effectiveness of failure estimation method and co-design method are verified based on the simulation example.
