AB  - Smart grid is a critical power infrastructure which includes many networked field devices such as Programmable Logic Controller (PLC), Remote Terminal Unit (RTU), status sensors, and smart meters. Securing the smart grid is complex yet essential for our daily lives. This paper presents security protocols for securing the communication, control and management in smart grids. Specifically, it presents a key agreement and update protocols based on symmetric-key primitives and smart grid topologies, that are able to efficiently detect and revoke compromised IEDs.
