AU  - M. Li
AU  - Y. -F. Zhang
T2  - 2025 IEEE 8th International Conference on Industrial Cyber-Physical Systems (ICPS)
AB  - In edge intelligent terminal devices for substation inspection, object detection algorithms are widely used, offering high efficiency and accuracy. However, convolutional neural network (CNN) methods rely on non-maximum suppression (NMS), which leads to increased network latency and unstable performance. Transformer-based detectors (DETR) face challenges in meeting low-cost detection requirements due to their computational cost and slow convergence speed. To address this issue, this paper proposes the Spatial-Channel Attention Transformer-based Detector (SCA-DETR). SCADETR features an efficient backbone network and hybrid encoder, integrating the Spatial-Channel Attention (SCA) mechanism to optimize global feature modeling and multi-scale feature fusion, significantly improving detection efficiency and accuracy. Experimental results on a substation inspection dataset demonstrate that SCA-DETR achieves optimal detection performance and lower computational demands, making it more suitable for deployment in edge intelligent terminal devices within substations.
