AB  - Traditional research and testing of data links mostly rely on highly abstracted and simplified combat simulation systems, which often fail to fully capture and simulate various limiting factors such as the complex and dynamic electromagnetic environment. Therefore, the difficulty of data link verification has always been a significant factor limiting the development of data links. This paper introduces the method of digital twins to reduce the difficulty of verification and testing of data link systems. Our team conducted the requirements analysis for the twin system of data links, and provided detailed explanations of the architecture design of the system. Finally, the effectiveness and consistency between virtual and physical systems functions of the current twin system are verified and analyzed through the establishment of experimental fields, demonstrating the virtual-to-real mapping function of the twin system for actual data link systems and the effectiveness of testing and verification of data link systems in subsequent experiments.
