AB  - Terrestrial and nonterrestrial networks (T-NTNs) are envisioned to support wide coverage and seamless connection for mobile terminals (e.g., the Internet of connected vehicles) by incorporating space networks, air networks, and terrestrial networks. To improve the service performance of the integrated networks, several potential issues have been investigated, e.g., reliable connections among the wireless devices and secure data transmission. In this article, motivated by the advanced digital twin (DT), we present the DT-oriented T-NTNs that build a virtual environment based on the physical information of the integrated networks to provide multidomain resource allocation. Specifically, we first introduce the framework of DT-oriented T-NTNs, which consists of the physical layer and the DT layer. Then, the distributed incentive scheme is designed to encourage resource provision from resource-rich wireless devices to resource-limited wireless devices. To further consider the security threats in T-NTNs, we formulate a collaborative blockchain for the integrated networks to guarantee secure resource management, in which each network segment of the T-NTNs maintains a specially designed blockchain to achieve collaboration. Finally, a case study of secure resource management for DT-oriented T-NTNs is illustrated to validate their performance in comparison with baseline schemes.
