TI  - Hybrid Genetic Algorithm and Fuzzy Control Approach for Lunar Lander Soft Landing
AU  - V. S. Oleynikov
AU  - G. Tianyi
T2  - 2026 ElCon Conference of Young Researchers in Electrical Engineering, Automation & Control Systems (ElCon-EE)
AB  - Lunar landing requires precise control of the descent trajectory to ensure both safety and fuel efficiency. This paper develops a practical control solution by combining the global optimization capability of genetic algorithms with the adaptive nature of fuzzy logic control. The initial conditions are set based on the Chang'e-3 mission profile, with an initial altitude of 15 km and horizontal velocity of 1.7 km/s[1]. The genetic algorithm generates an optimal reference trajectory by considering fuel consumption and various operational constraints. Fuzzy control rules are then formulated based on this trajectory to handle the real-time control task during landing. The fuzzy controller continuously adjusts the thrust to maintain trajectory tracking while accommodating disturbances and model uncertainties. Simulation results indicate that the proposed method achieves consistent landing performance with good accuracy and robustness, making it suitable for autonomous lunar landing missions.
