AU  - K. Srividya
AU  - A. Rajulapati
AU  - R.Haranath
AU  - S. Vijayakumar
AU  - M. N. Swapna Sri
AU  - N. Dhasarathan
T2  - 2025 5th International Conference on Ubiquitous Computing and Intelligent Information Systems (ICUIS)
AB  - Fault-tolerant mechanisms are required in conventional methods to provide safety, operation and resiliency continuation. Fault-Tolerant Control Systems (FTCS) are mainly based on static models for pre-determined logic and they are not flexible sufficient to adapt for developing fault situations. This paper presented and discussed Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS), Internet of Things (IoT), and Reinforcement Learning (RL). The combination CPS-IoT-RL was developed as a stratified system which implemented cyber, perception, and control the domains. It allows autonomous protection against faults, recovery in dynamic industrial processes by using real-time data acquisition, cyber-physical analytics, and DRL algorithms DQN, DDPG, PPO, SAC are implemented to facilitate intelligent decision-making in diverse fault situations to optimize system behaviour. The framework is established by a sequence of pecific scenarios in industries including energy grids, intelligent manufacturing, and chemical processes. The findings show that there are substantial improvements in recovery accuracy, fault detection delay, overall uptimes, and control performance. The combination of CPS and IoT infrastructure with the adaptive learning strength of RL in the proposed solution preconditions the next generation of scalable and cyber-resilient industrial control systems in the real-time world with high security and performance rates.
