AU  - A. W. Rohde
AU  - T. Stander
T2  - 2025 Asia-Pacific Microwave Conference (APMC)
AB  - This study proposes a single port method to extract the dielectric constant of materials using digital-twinning from simulation. Unlike classical methods, this method allows for samples of arbitrary size which is advantageous in cases where thin sample sections can not be manufactured, such as stereo-lithographic 3D printed resins. The method also eliminates errors due to air gaps by curing the liquid 3D printed resins inside the sample holders. The X-band dielectric constants for Formlabs White, Black, and High Temperature resins are extracted using the proposed method, and are shown to compare well with two-port characterisation using the classical Nicholson-Ross-Weir method.
