AB  - Stricter emission guidelines, lower operation costs and increasing environmental awareness among end consumers are driving the global rise in the share of electrified vehicles. This trend encompasses not only passenger cars but also two- and three-wheelers, buses, trucks, agricultural equipment, maritime, aviation and heavy machinery. In the dynamic field of battery system development, enhancing development efficiency and reducing time to market are crucial for maintaining technological leadership and achieving best-in-class product costs. This paper presents advanced methodologies for a structured and focused testing regimen that significantly reduces the development time and costs without compromising the battery performance, safety, or quality targets. The analysis centers on two primary approaches: the implementation of precise testing protocols to achieve first-time-right outcomes and the utilization of advanced computational methods to streamline test cases. These strategies collectively enable a substantial reduction in test time, thereby enhancing the overall development efficiency while consistently upholding quality and safety standards. The paper concludes with recommendations for best practices, emphasizing continuous innovation and adaptive strategies. This streamlined battery development process ensures that new products reach the market faster and at lower development costs.
