AB  - The paper encompasses energy exhaustion attacks directed to nodes of quickly deployable wireless networks for crisis management. Such networks are used to solve various problems associated with the collection, processing and monitoring of data from sensors set up in a physical environment. Denial-of-Sleep attacks are simulated on terminal devices based on Arduino microcircuits, communicational interfaces Digi XBee s2 and intermediate network equipment. In order to form specific rules for Denial-of-Sleep attack detection we singled out a set of traffic features and analyzed both normal and attacking traffic within an experimental testbed. Detection quality is confirmed on testing traffic recorded within the experimental study.
