AB  - The multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) control problem of Multi-Active-Bridge converter can be effectively addressed by model predictive control method, while the input and output constraints can also be included to ensure safety operation and system protection. However, solving the constrained MPC problem online within a short sampling time poses a huge computational challenge. To address these issues, the real-time implementation of CCS-MPC on a low-cost microcontroller unit (MCU) is discussed including problem formulation, QP solver deployment, and real-time certification. Finally, the developed CCS-MPC scheme is experimentally verified by a four-port MAB converter and demonstrates the over/under voltage protection capability and real-time certification.
