AU  - H. Tang
AU  - Y. Yang
AU  - Q. Wan
AU  - H. Guan
AU  - B. Fu
T2  - 2025 IEEE International Conference on Unmanned Systems (ICUS)
AB  - Lifeboats are crucial tools for emergency rescue on ships, and the uncertainty of slamming during their release process is one of the challenges in optimizing lifeboat design. To overcome the drawbacks of traditional lifeboat slamming simulations that require a significant amount of computational time and resources, a data-driven hybrid model is developed to achieve the prediction of lifeboat time-domain slamming at different positions. This model combines advanced intelligent algorithms such as CNN, BiLSTM, and attention mechanisms to comprehensively learn the nonlinear relationship between the lifeboat motion status and slamming load. By comparing with different data-driven models, the advantages of this hybrid model were further verified. This research will provide technical support for the autonomous rescue of smart ships and facilitate the establishment of a digital twin system for lifeboats.
