AB  - Traditional cooperative guidance laws for multimissile systems face challenges in simultaneously achieving precise time synchronization and minimal terminal miss distance. To address this limitation, we propose a novel hybrid intelligent guidance framework integrating Zero-Effort-Miss prediction and dynamic time coordination. The ZEM module leverages optimal control theory to predict and correct miss trajectories, while the time coordination module dynamically adjusts impact timing through feedback error compensation. This fusion enables concurrent optimization of spatial precision and temporal coordination. Simulations demonstrate that the proposed method significantly improves both guidance accuracy and time synchronization compared to conventional approaches, providing a robust solution for cyber-physical weapon systems operating in complex environments. The framework establishes a new paradigm for intelligent cooperative control.
