AB  - Shortly, electric vehicles (EVs) will make up the bulk of the automobile company, producing massive volumes of statistics for additional studies. This paper outlines a methodology for analyzing electric vehicle data, focusing specifically on energy consumption. The database compiled for this study includes data from 123 electric vehicles. Dabl API library is used in Python for data analysis. Based on the data classification. The results were presented on the classification of data with categorical and continuous features according to the selected parameters. Moreover, the selected parameters are considered for calculating the energy consumption of electric vehicles using a dataset collected using an online database for the study parameters. The data classification revealed no correlation between energy consumption and charging speed. However, a positive correlation was observed for the maximum velocity and range of parameters. Conversely, a correlation was found between energy consumption and the factor of 100 km/hspeed and the parameters with 100 km/h acceleration. The presented methodology for assessing electric vehicle data can be scaled to other datasets for preparing data to create machine learning models.
