AU  - S. Leng
AU  - T. Quek
T2  - IEEE Communications Magazine
AB  - The evaluation from the Internet of Things (IoT) to the Internet of Everything (IoE) has achieved the intelligent connection among massive IoT devices. In this context, the emerging Internet of Agents (IoA) is emerging to perform a fundamental shift in the digital paradigm for intelligent cognition. The IoA is expected to enable autonomous cooperation for intelligent applications, such as robots-based intelligent logistics. The IoA can envision a cognition-centric ecosystem in which intelligent robots perform cooperative sensing and reasoning. To achieve this goal, this article designs a terminal-edge cooperative Large Language Model (LLM) framework. It can achieve accurate service provisions by integrating cross-layer computing resources for IoA scenarios. In addition, our framework can enable robots to perform autonomous decision-making instead of requesting from the cloud or the edge servers for real-time service provisions. Based on our framework, we provide several potential IoA scenarios with detailed analysis. A case study of robots-based parcel sorting and handling is selected to validate the feasibility and effectiveness of our framework. The experiment results show that our framework achieves a high parcel sorting accuracy of up to 95% with a low delivery latency of under 1 second compared to traditional centralized manners on average, respectively.
